de.unistuttgart.vis.wearable.os.parcel

Class PSensorData

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.unistuttgart.vis.wearable.os.parcel.PSensorData
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PSensorData, PSensorData

    public class PSensorData
extends java.lang.Object
    Parcelable Sensor Data object. This class represents a list of SensorData objects but optimizes them considering their data layout to be sent through the parcel. The typical use of this class will be to create a new PSensorData object from a List of SensorData objects and after this object has been sent to the client call the toSensorDataList() method to create the initial List of SensorData objects. Note that this class should only be used in the APIInternalBinder class as well as in the APIFunctions class.
    Author:
    roehrdor
